com.inqwell.any

Class AnyMapConstDecor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AnyMapConstDecor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Composite, Map, Serializable, Cloneable

    public final class AnyMapConstDecor
extends Object
implements Map, Cloneable
    Provides a decorator to ensure that the hashCode() and equals() methods apply such that different instances containing the same underlying Any yield the same result.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • AnyMapConstDecor

        public AnyMapConstDecor(Map m)
        Wrap a Map to bestow identity semantics. See also Identity.bestowIdentity(). Only these functions can be used to set up identity semantics, hence this constructor is restricted to package access.

        public boolean hasIdentity()
        Description copied from interface: Composite
        Determine whether a Composite instance is a managed object. Being managed means that hashCode() and equals() operate on the object instance itself rather than the instance's members. This means that the instance can be tracked where it is important to ensure that multiple threads are dealing with physically the same object.
